@page "/installation"

<PageTitle>Installation | Spillgebees.Blazor.Map</PageTitle>

<h1>Installation</h1>

<h2>NuGet Package</h2>

<p>Add the package to your project:</p>

<CodeBlock Language="bash" Files="@(new Dictionary<string, string>
{
    ["Terminal"] = "dotnet add package Spillgebees.Blazor.Map",
})" />

<h2>JavaScript Module</h2>

<p>
    No script tags are required. The library ships with a <code>lib.module.js</code> file that Blazor
    loads automatically via the standard <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/aspnet/core/blazor/javascript-interoperability/javascript-isolation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JS module isolation</a> convention.
    The MapLibre GL JS bundle is included, so no CDN reference is needed.
</p>

<h2>Minimal Usage</h2>

<p>
    Add the component to any Razor page or component. A fixed height is required for the map to render.
</p>

<CodeBlock Language="razor" Files="@_minimalUsage" />

<h2>Changing the Map Style</h2>

<p>
    When no style is specified, the map defaults to <strong>OpenFreeMap Liberty</strong>, a clean vector style
    with no API key required. To use a different style, pass it via <code>MapOptions.Style</code>:
</p>

<CodeBlock Language="razor" Files="@_styleUsage" />

@code {
    private static readonly Dictionary<string, string> _minimalUsage = new()
    {
        ["MyPage.razor"] = """
            @using Spillgebees.Blazor.Map.Components
            @using Spillgebees.Blazor.Map.Models

            <SgbMap MapOptions="@_mapOptions" Height="500px" />

            @code {
                private readonly MapOptions _mapOptions = new(
                    Center: new Coordinate(51.505, -0.09),
                    Zoom: 13
                );
            }
            """,
    };

    private static readonly Dictionary<string, string> _styleUsage = new()
    {
        ["MyPage.razor"] = """
            <SgbMap MapOptions="@_mapOptions" Height="500px" />

            @code {
                private readonly MapOptions _mapOptions = new(
                    Center: new Coordinate(51.505, -0.09),
                    Zoom: 13,
                    Style: MapStyle.OpenFreeMap.Bright
                );
            }
            """,
    };
}

<p>
    Other built-in presets are <code>MapStyle.OpenFreeMap.Positron</code> and <code>MapStyle.OpenStreetMap.Standard</code>.
    For any other source use <code>MapStyle.FromUrl</code>, <code>MapStyle.FromWmsUrl</code>,
    <code>MapStyle.FromWmtsUrl</code>, or <code>MapStyle.FromArcGisMapServer</code>.
    See the <a href="components/sgb-map#styles">Styles</a> example for more detail.
</p>
